<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>If the nominal interest rate is 8% and inflation is expected to be 3%, what is the real interest rate?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">11%</option>
            <option letter="b">5%</option>
            <option letter="c">2.67%</option>
            <option letter="d">-5%</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The real interest rate equals the nominal interest rate minus the expected inflation rate. In this case, 8% - 3% = 5%. This represents the actual return on investment after accounting for the erosion of purchasing power due to inflation.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
